Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Cut the @tomato{2%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Trim the @Brussels sprouts{100%g} and quarter through the root.

Quarter, core and grate the @apple{1}(grated) (no need to peel). Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, wrap each @British Hickory smoked sausage{2} in 2 rashers of @British streaky bacon{4} - starting at the top, spiral the rashers down the sausage one after another so the whole thing is covered.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop the sausages onto a baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

While everything bakes, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the sprouts to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Allow to cook until the sprouts are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer to a medium #bowl{} and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @dried cranberries{30%g} and tomato. Cook until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @tomato ketchup{2} and @sugar{1/2}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium. Simmer until the tomatoes have broken down and the sauce is thick, ~{6-7%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Once cooked, taste and add @salt{}, @pepper{} or @sugar{} if needed, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, add the @burger sauce{60%g}, @coleslaw mix{120%g} and grated apple to the sprouts. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well.

Pop the buns into the oven to warm through for ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, pop the buns on your plates and spoon in the cranberry ketchup. Sprinkle in the cheese, then finish with a giant pig in blanket.

Serve with the wedges and sprout slaw alongside.

Enjoy!